---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Insulation Cardinia Lakes | NatHERS 7-Star New Build Specialists | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Insulation for Cardinia Lakes — NatHERS 7-star first-fit wall and ceiling batts, R6.0+ cold-microclimate upgrades, media-room acoustic, NCC F5 party walls for terrace lots. Arcadia, Timbertop, Estuary."
  canonical="https://beaconsfieldinsulation.com.au/cardinia-lakes/">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Cardinia Lakes &middot; Arcadia &middot; Timbertop &middot; Estuary</span>
      <h1>Insulation in <span class="accent">Cardinia Lakes</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Cardinia Lakes is NatHERS 7-star new-build country &mdash; young
        families in 2018+ estate homes that meet the modern minimum R-values
        out of the box. The conversation here is about first-fit wall and
        ceiling batts (we work with the volume builders), top-ups to
        R6.0/R7.0 for cold-microclimate comfort, acoustic batts in media
        rooms, and NCC F5 party-wall compliance for terrace lots.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free assessment</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Cardinia Lakes</span>
      <h2>The Cardinia Lakes insulation story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>NatHERS 7-star is the starting point, not the target.</h3>
        <p>
          Almost every Cardinia Lakes home built post-2018 was designed to
          meet NatHERS 7-star &mdash; R5.0+ ceiling, R2.7 total system walls,
          R2.0 underfloor (where applicable), anti-condensation sarking.
          That's better than 90% of the existing Cardinia Shire stock. But
          R5.0 ceiling is still the <strong>minimum</strong>, and for Cardinia
          Lakes' cold-pocket winter mornings we usually recommend upgrading
          to R6.0 or R7.0 &mdash; $1&ndash;$3/m&sup2; extra for noticeably
          warmer bedrooms.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Small block, open-plan, lots of glass.</h3>
        <p>
          Typical Cardinia Lakes estate lot is 350&ndash;500m&sup2;, with a
          new-build floor plan that's heavy on glass and open-plan living.
          The insulation envelope has to work hard against that &mdash; even
          a properly-spec'd R5.0 ceiling can feel under-served on a 5&deg;C
          July morning if the home has 30m&sup2; of glazing on a south-facing
          wall. Upgrading ceiling to R7.0 plus adding under-rafter radiant
          barrier for summer is the standard premium pathway.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Terrace lots and dual-occ &mdash; NCC F5.</h3>
        <p>
          Cardinia Lakes has a growing terrace and dual-occupancy footprint
          (Arcadia and Timbertop releases especially). NCC F5 party-wall
          compliance (Rw + Ctr &ge; 50) is required and routinely gets missed
          or under-spec'd by volume builders. We install Knauf Earthwool
          Acoustic R2.5 in the party-wall cavity with the required resilient-
          channel or staggered-stud construction, and coordinate compliance
          testing at completion. Don't accept a "thermal" batt in a party
          wall &mdash; the acoustic rating is what NCC F5 needs.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Media rooms &mdash; the missing batt.</h3>
        <p>
          About 70% of Cardinia Lakes media rooms we audit have R2.5 thermal
          batts in the walls and ceiling but no acoustic upgrade. Adding
          acoustic batts ($4.5K&ndash;$9K for a 4&times;5m room) is the most
          requested upgrade we do post-occupancy. Easiest done during build
          or before plasterboard goes up &mdash; we coordinate with builders.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Cardinia Lakes jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>NatHERS 7-star first-fit wall + ceiling batts on new build ($4K&ndash;$8K)</li>
          <li>R5.0 &rarr; R7.0 ceiling top-up post-occupancy ($3K&ndash;$5K)</li>
          <li>Media-room acoustic upgrade ($4.5K&ndash;$9K)</li>
          <li>NCC F5 party-wall acoustic in terrace lots ($180&ndash;$280/m&sup2;)</li>
          <li>Under-rafter radiant barrier for summer heat ($22&ndash;$35/m&sup2;)</li>
          <li>Garage-conversion insulation for new home office ($2K&ndash;$4K)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/beaconsfield/">Beaconsfield</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/officer/">Officer</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/pakenham/">Pakenham</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/heritage-springs/">Heritage Springs</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cardinia-shire/">All Cardinia Shire</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Cardinia Lakes insulation assessment.</h2>
        <p>First-fit, top-up or acoustic. NCC F5 party-wall compliance handled.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
